&lt;h1 id="how-to-raise-money"&gt;How to Raise Money&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Want to start a startup? Get funded by Y Combinator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;September 2013&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most startups that raise money do it more than once. A typical trajectory might be (1) to get started with a few tens of thousands from something like Y Combinator or individual angels, then (2) raise a few hundred thousand to a few million to build the company, and then (3) once the company is clearly succeeding, raise one or more later rounds to accelerate growth.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>The Unbundling of the Venture Capital Industry</title><link>https://linguista.cn/person/naval/orig/the-unbundling-of-the-venture-capital-industry/</link><pubDate>Wed, 01 Dec 2010 01:05:13 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/person/naval/orig/the-unbundling-of-the-venture-capital-industry/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/person/naval/zh/the-unbundling-of-the-venture-capital-industry.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
